    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Top-down shot of Razer Basilisk V3 Pro on a blue and green background" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9P4DXeJHJWuCwFeBgKQktEPwWbY=/0x0:2550x1700/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73505304/236715_Best_gaming_mouse_AKrales_0083.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;Razer’s wireless V3 Pro packs a 30K DPI sensor, 11 programmable inputs, and all the lighting effects you could want.&lt;/em&gt; | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="Xk2xS6"&gt;Logitech’s new G309 &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/9/24194631/logitech-g309-gaming-mouse-powerplay"&gt;might be one of the most versatile gaming mice&lt;/a&gt; in existence, but before that, there was our &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/21252193/best-gaming-mouse"&gt;No. 1 pick for the best gaming mouse&lt;/a&gt;: the &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2022/8/23/23313085/razer-basilisk-v3-pro-deathadder-gaming-mouse"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Razer Basilisk V3 Pro&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. And now, thanks to a $30 discount, Razer’s claw-shaped peripheral is available at &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0B6Y3XYFG/?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://howl.me/cmPfzJzWl50"&gt;Best Buy&lt;/a&gt; in black or white for $129.99, its lowest price to date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"&gt;&lt;aside id="YPTyBf"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="readmore" data-anthem-component-data='{"stories":[{"title":"Logitech CEO Hanneke Faber wants your next mouse to last forever","url":"https://www.theverge.com/24206847/logitech-ceo-hanneke-faber-mouse-keyboard-gaming-decoder-podcast-interview"},{"title":"The new Logitech G Pro X Superlight 2 gives me serious mouse envy","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/5/23043644/logitech-g-pro-x-superlight-2-gaming-mouse-price-release-date-specs"},{"title":"Razer beats Wooting to a speedy new keyboard feature for PC gaming","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/9/24194977/razer-snap-tap-mode-huntsman-v3-pro-wooting-rappy-snappy"}]}'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/aside&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="PTxlbC"&gt;Despite having the same shape and layout as the standard V3, the step-up V3 Pro offers Razer’s third-gen optical switches, a more powerful 30K DPI sensor, and 1,000Hz wireless connectivity (or a polling rate of up to 4,000Hz if you add the &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.com/Razer-Mouse-Dock-Wireless-Charging-PC/dp/B0B7VB5NPX?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;optional wireless charging dock&lt;/a&gt;). The comfortable mouse also features a hyperfast scroll wheel — which can automatically switch to smooth scrolling based on how fast you...&lt;/p&gt;
